instance virtual_to_physical_interaction : DTDFVocab:VirtualToPhysical [
    base:desc "Control commands originate from the DT’s supervisory controller as JSON payloads published to RabbitMQ queues. Each command contains a target device (e.g., fan, heatbed), desired state (ON/OFF, speed, temperature set‑point) and a priority flag. The Raspberry Pi subscribes to these queues, validates the payload signature against a locally stored HMAC key, authenticates the publisher via AMQPS, and forwards the instruction to the corresponding actuator through a dedicated GPIO interface. The system collects feedback via the 1‑Wire bus sensors and acknowledges receipt and execution by publishing an acknowledgment message back to the DT, thereby closing the control loop and preventing command conflicts via a first‑come‑first‑served arbitration algorithm."
]

instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
